<br>
Would that ability really matter? How often are you in front of a MOB?<br>
<br>
I mean, it sounds nice on paper, but I'd say %95 of the time I'm behind a mob.<br>
<br>
So 95% of the time I have a chance to land a full backstab.<br>
<br>
Why would I care to land a minimum backstab from the front when there's many other skills to put points into?<br>
<br>
That's just my take. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usolann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 10:30:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP per point.</span><hr size=1> looking at the PvP point of view this would improves rogues damage output <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upherret.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pherret</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 10:32:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP per point.</span><hr size=1> In a normal group situation, I would agree with you but there are times when I'm physically unable to get around to the back of the mob or it's pingponging around.  I'd rather have that minimum backstab than nothing.  <br>
<br>
I would guess it's pretty handy for times when you're forced to solo.  ~100 extra dmg every 6 seconds isn't anything insignificant.  <br>
<br>
I would take the other skills before this one however. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzeik2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeik2001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/7/01 3:57:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP per point.</span><hr size=1> &quot;Chaotic Stab: (1 skill level - cost 6 skill points) - This ability allows the Rogue to do his minimum backstab damage on any backstab attempt, even if that attempt is not made while behind the opponent.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Does that mean you'll NEVER miss with a Backstab? It's what it sounds like, but it could mean other things too...<br>
<br>
&quot;edit, oh and even if not, well, being able to stab from the front with say, FOR EXAMPLE, a 3 damage weapon for 120 at level 60... well, thats pretty good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzeik2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeik2001</A> at: 12/7/01 3:58:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utotteswede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotteSwede</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/7/01 4:44:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP per point.</span><hr size=1> If it lands every BS (min dmg if from front) then it´s a decent upgrade to dmg for rogues. I for one miss a lot of backstabs (especially on high AC mobs) and the added 120 (plus maybe check for double BS on each ?) sounds good to me.<br>
<br>
We´ll see later I guess...<br>
<br>
-Fubbik- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uavrus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avrus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/7/01 10:08:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP per point.</span><hr size=1> &quot;If it lands every BS (min dmg if from front) then it´s a decent upgrade to dmg for rogues. I for one miss a lot of backstabs (especially on high AC mobs) and the added 120 (plus maybe check for double BS on each ?) sounds good to me&quot;<br>
<br>
Hrm, I dunno. The description is vague.  If it means you hit with every backstab attempt then it is indeed a big improvement.<br>
<br>
If it's just taken as it's read that you can do minimum backstab damage from the front ... then it doesn't seem like a worth while upgrade to me. Because, we already do minimum backstab damage from the back ... IF we hit. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uavrus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avrus</A> at: 12/7/01 10:10:03 am<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers>The Back Alley</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
